We file income tax returns in the U.S. federal jurisdiction and various state, local and foreign jurisdictions. As a large taxpayer, our income tax returns
are regularly audited by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) and other taxing authorities. The IRS has completed field examinations of our tax returns
through 2010. All audit periods prior to 2003 are closed for federal examination purposes. Contested issues from our 2003 through 2010 returns are at
various stages of resolution with the IRS Appeals Division. While we do not expect material changes, we are generally unable to estimate the range of
impacts on the balance of uncertain tax positions or the impact on the effective tax rate from the resolution of these issues until the close of the
examination process; and it is possible that the amount of unrecognized benefit with respect to our uncertain tax positions could increase or decrease
within the next 12 months.
 
